metadata.title: Keyboard Concerto No. 5 in F minor
metadata.tempo: Movement I: Allegro moderato; Movement II: Largo; Movement III: Presto
metadata.timeSignature: Movement I: 2/4; Movement II: 4/4; Movement III: 3/8
metadata.derivedFrom: Possibly Violin Concerto (lost) or Oboe Concerto
metadata.description: One of Bach's most beloved keyboard concertos, particularly famous for its serene Largo movement (also known as 'Arioso')

keyboardMapping.description: Notes mapped sequentially to keyboard keys

sections.name: Movement I - Allegro moderato
sections.description: Opening movement in ritornello form with virtuosic keyboard passages

phrases.description: First solo episode - virtuosic passage work

sections.name: Movement II - Largo (Arioso)
sections.description: The famous slow movement, one of Bach's most beloved pieces, featuring a noble, singing melody

sections.name: Movement III - Presto
sections.description: Brilliant concluding movement with rapid passage work and driving rhythms

practiceSettings.specialNotes: The famous Largo movement should be played very expressively; the outer movements require crisp articulation
